<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="595" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="595">General distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="595">From SE European Russia and the Caucasus to SE West Siberia and W Mongolia, Iran (the northern parts and Zagros), N Afghanistan.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="595" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="595">Local distribution and ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="595">This species was (and is) distributed over the dry steppes in the south-western part of the region. Its rare populations are associated with short scarce vegetation on clay soils. It is relatively common in the semi-deserts of E Kazakhstan.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
